FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1777071785
OL,3,CFirst Minister 'very comfortable' with
OL,4,Cdefence growth deal announcement
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FMs O'Neill and deputy First Minister
OL,8,FEmma Little-Pengelly have previously
OL,9,Fcalled for a meeting with Sir Keir
OL,10,FStarmer to discuss budget challenges
OL,11,Fin Northern Ireland.
OL,13,FHowever, she rejected the argument
OL,14,Fthat the Executive is continually
OL,15,Fgoing to the UK Government "with a
OL,16,Fbegging bowl".
OL,26,@wD@\OUxD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1777071785
OL,3,CFirst Minister 'very comfortable' with
OL,4,Cdefence growth deal announcement
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,F"Why should the public here pay more
OL,8,Fthan their counterparts whenever they
OL,9,Fpay their taxes, and businesses here
OL,10,Fpay their VAT. We're not asking for
OL,11,Fspecial treatment. We're asking for
OL,12,Ffairness and equality, and we're
OL,13,Funderfunded in comparison to both
OL,14,FScotland and Wales. So if that's your
OL,15,Fstarting point, you're off to a
OL,16,Freally, really sticky start. We're
OL,17,Fprepared to do our part in terms of
OL,18,Freform. We're prepared to do our part
OL,19,Fin terms of trying to deliver public
OL,20,Fservices in a more efficient way, be
OL,21,Finnovative, use technology. We will do
OL,22,Fall of those things. We will weed out
OL,23,Finefficiency. But we're not prepared
OL,24,Fto ask the public to pay more at a
OL,25,Ftime whenever they are really getting
OL,26,Fit tight because of all the volatility
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,44811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1777071785
OL,3,CFirst Minister 'very comfortable' with
OL,4,Cdefence growth deal announcement
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FMs O'Neill also reaffirmed her
OL,8,Fcommitment to the Casement Park and A5
OL,9,Froad projects, both of which are key
OL,10,Fpriorities for Sinn Fein in the
OL,11,FExecutive.
OL,13,FSome demolition work began at Casement
OL,14,FPark earlier this year where plans for
OL,15,Fa 34,000-capacity stadium at the site
OL,16,Fhave been delayed because of a major
OL,17,Ffunding shortfall.
OL,26,@rD@Vrr
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1777071785
OL,3,CFirst Minister 'very comfortable' with
OL,4,Cdefence growth deal announcement
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FSinn Fein Finance Minister John O'Dowd
OL,8,Fhas pledged more than #100 million for
OL,9,Fthe redevelopment in his draft budget
OL,10,Fthat is currently out for
OL,11,Fconsultation, but has not been agreed
OL,12,Fby other Executive parties.
OL,14,FMs O'Neill said: "Casement Park will
OL,15,Fbe built. Casement Park will be in
OL,16,Fprogress whenever we go to the
OL,17,Felection, because diggers are already
OL,18,Fin the ground at Casement Park.
OL,19,FThey'll need to move on to the next
OL,20,Fstage of all the remedial works, and
OL,21,Fthen we need to get the project built."
OL,26,@vD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
